Preconditions:
The array `arr` must be initialized and contain at least one element.
The values of `left` and `right` must be valid indices within the range of the array `arr`.
The value of `left` must be less than or equal to the value of `right`.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the frequency of the given `value` in the subarray `arr[left...right]`.
The method should return -1 if the value of `left` is greater than the value of `right`.
The method should return 0 if the subarray `arr[left...right]` does not contain the given `value`.
The method should return the correct frequency of the given `value` in the subarray `arr[left...right]` as per the requirements provided.